<paragraph id="30FB77CF8B538424F36965CC87A0F487" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">McPherson (1980: 89).</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="CFFE6CFB4DBAF5A2BCFB991ED84E230D" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="1542D114B36D031B93E2F642CDBF822C" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C5CF377BCB8EA3B383764ABB84B5D307" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">A little known species, apparently endemic to Guerrero State in Mexico.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="150D6CC6B209BB07AFFAD6C4379791BD" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis id="2BF8B9DD2C27E9A1C3A80E258D02F3F9" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">MEXICO. Guerrero</emphasis>
: Casa Verde, 
<emphasis id="C0E18F411C7E8C756095F40BF359C4FB" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">H. Kruse</emphasis>
s.n. [14/2/1970] (MEXU); Eduardo Neri, Venta Vieja, 
<emphasis id="8010C18DDDC01E56B4656AFF565E4F2A" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">A. A. Aguilar</emphasis>
34 (MEXU); Zopilote canyon, Chilpancingo -
<normalizedToken id="12DCB6CD17B1C6482C21378FD946173B" originalValue="Río">Rio</normalizedToken>
Balsas, 
<emphasis id="E902C2B14911DA9B2227F899452DB382" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">B. Mostul</emphasis>
1161A (OXF).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="4F248D6B49F7746075DC2AA3503F0777" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="notes">
<paragraph id="E0384AF56703F2173C7801B800485212" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="EDCF14FF93C4415AAA5E839548050963" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
The large, nearly white, sericeous corolla, the subequal sericeous sepals and the included anthers distinguish this species, which is leafless when flowering. There is one leaf on 
<emphasis id="3A82985FF5B1E336F1AADDA7BC61019D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Aguilar</emphasis>
34. It is 4.5 
<normalizedToken id="D36CD0A4FE39F81388FA783B8A4CAE72" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
4 cm, suborbicular, abruptly acute, basally cuneate, glabrous, abaxially white, strongly reticulate.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
